=== Critical reception ===
"The Good, the Bad and the Cuddly" received generally positive reviews from critics. '''Barney Morris''' (June 3, 1910 – May 24, 1962) was an American professional [[baseball]] [[pitcher]] in the [[Negro leagues]], the [[Mexican League]], and the [[Minor league baseball|minor league]] [[Manitoba-Dakota League]]. His research has contributed to the development of linguistic corpora and computational resources for Indian languages, particularly [[Bengali language|Bengali]], and to interdisciplinary work in linguistics and the digital humanities.

== Early life and education ==
